ightly modified with the panic calls) will panic with \"0x0\" in the if-clause, which looks like a regression to me:\r\n```rust\r\npub fn get_proc_address(&self, addr: &str) -> *const () {\r\n        let addr = CString::new(addr.as_bytes()).unwrap();\r\n        let addr_ptr = addr.as_ptr();\r\n        let p = unsafe { gl::wgl::GetProcAddress(addr_ptr) as *const _ };\r\n        if !p.is_null() {\r\n            panic!(\"{:?}\", p);\r\n            return p;\r\n        }\r\n        panic!(\"How?\");\r\n        unsafe { kernel32::GetProcAddress(self.gl_library, addr_ptr) as *const _ }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nThis only appears in release mode, debug runs correctly.\r\n\r\nWindows 10, MSVC 15.3.3 2017\r\n`rustc 1.23.0-nightly (63739ab7b 2017-11-21)`\r\n\r\nReproduction is a bit trickier:\r\nRun `cargo run --example triangle --release` in our `gfx-rs/pre-ll` [branch](https://github.com/gfx-rs/gfx/tree/pre-ll) should crash on loading the function pointers, boiling down to the issue noted above.", "closed_by": {"login": "msiglreith", "id": 7253845, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcyNTM4NDU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7253845?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith", "html_url": "https://github.com/msiglreith", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/msiglreith/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "h